node.text:
Growing into this new role of #motherhood whilst retaining the parts of me previously loved.
.
I don’t bother rolling out my mat any more because it’s near impossible to have a full hour of practice. 😅 Looking forward to the days of longer, nightmare-free naps. Meanwhile, I’ll take what I can whilst chasing away monsters from my little one. #MamaandGen | 15mins practice sped up 10x.
.
#yoga #yogapractice #momlife #sgmommies #sgmom #sgmummy #sgbaby #7weekspostpartum #fitness #postnatalyoga #inversions #pinchamayurasana #forearmstand #babygirl #yogimom
@senoritayogini 😅😅 it’s like learning how to press all over again. So hard now!
@hanadoesyoga I wasn’t smelling her 😅. She had a nightmare and started crying. Why do babies cry so often whilst sleeping?
@pinkchampagne13 i know you weren’t smelling her, i’m smelling her (from here, virtually 😂 #creepyaunty)! i don’t think it’s nightmares, they are just easily startled at this age!
@hanadoesyoga 🤣 and newborns are so noisy when they sleep! I didn’t know that. 🧐 creepy auntie, u can play with her after #circuitbreakerSG, start training your arms now. She’ll prob be 6kg by then.
@crackedcrockpot it’s a gift! Brand’s candide expert from @pupsik_mom #pupsikstudio ☺️
@pinkchampagne13 is that the dockatot or what kind of sleeping pad did you pick?
Babies go up very fast! Enjoy to the max😍

@anchal_sharma88 depends on your pre-pregnancy fitness level, how active you are throughout pregnancy and how you feel after. The general guidelines are 4-6 weeks for natural delivery and 6-8 weeks or longer for C-sect delivery. Always check with your attending doctor for health clearance before resuming practice. Slow and steady is always better for longevity.
How soon can u resume the full practice after a delivery ?
You are such an inspiration to me, Ruth ❤️ Nothing stops you from practicing. Truly no pain no gain. 👏👏
Love your flow with your mini! 💙😍
